node.text: The video cut off but basically I wanted to tell you guys that I love you. It’s okay to feel overwhelmed right now - sit with that emotion. Like any storm - they all eventually pass. We are all going through challenging times in our own way based on our personal experience - some are concerned about losing jobs, some already lost their jobs, the business owners are concerned about their businesses and how they will continue employing people in such uncertain times - it’s very strange times we are living in because this is a gloabal issue right now. I’m not here to tell you that things are going to magically be alright - they are not. I’m just asking you to be kind to yourself and others, to do your best to just take it one day at a time - because thinking long term just feels way too overwhelming for all of us. Together - as humanity, we WILL get through this. I love you! May you always be happy, may you always be healthy, may you always be peaceful. Xx Mimi

node.text:
In times like now it’s so important to take care of your emotional hygiene - stay informed but avoid overconsumption of news, only consume news from very reputable sources, practice gratitude for what you have, focus on all the good that exists in your life, take time off social media and television, spend time with family or reconnect to yourself. Read books, meditate, journal, contemplate on your life and your purpose in it. 
Help others - especially if you have elderly friends, neighbours - ask them if you can buy groceries for them or run some errands, as many of them are afraid to go out at the moment. Wash your hands a lot, every time you enter somewhere - wash them again or use hand sanitizer. 
Stay calm ( panicking and being paranoid is the worst form of action right now). Avoid social gatherings, avoid sending your kids to school ( if you can), work from home ( if you can). Be mindful and intentional with your actions - it’s more important than ever. We are being tested at the moment and how we react to this experience will determine our future. There is so much we can do right now to raise our global vibrations - send love and kindness to all affected and locked. Love is a powerful energy and can travel virtually far and wide. Love is healing 🙏 Share something positive with yourself and others around you - what we focus on, we create. 
May you all be happy and healthy. Love, Mimi

node.text: Have you ever wondered how you make people feel around you? Whether your family or friends, colleagues at work, schoolmates at your school or strangers that you get to meet daily. Every interaction with others - we send out signals with our body language, eye contact, the words and tone we choose to use and of course the words we choose to speak to others. It all leaves an impact on others whether positive or negative. The beauty is that we have full control of our special power and how we use it daily with intention and awareness. Share this message with those you love ❤️👇🏻

node.text: I get so many DMs everyday about how to transition away from plastic. It’s definitely a journey- I’m still new to it myself and learning something new everyday. I still have lots of plastic around the house from the past and will use every single item until it’s done and finished before replacing with none plastic alternatives. What I can say is that it’s easier than I thought and it feels great. 🙏❤️

node.text: I get so many DMs about the topic of transitioning away from plastic and how to do it. I’m still new to this myself - I’m learning something new everyday, I’m not perfect at it, I still have tons of plastic from the past in my house, also I’m not zero waste. My intention and goal is to reduce my waste and live a low waste lifestyle. So far I have been loving this journey and instead of feeling stressed about it - I realised it’s easier than I thought it was. Also, I feel better - mentally and emotionally as a byproduct. I feel lighter in a way... 🙏❤️ let me know if you have experienced the same if you live a low waste lifestyle. Also, let me know if you have any specific questions in regards to this and I will be happy to answer below ❤️👇🏻👇🏻👇🏻

node.title: How I am transitioning away from plastic

node.text: Here is how I travel with one carry on for two months in the summer. I pack light dresses made of silk, light cotton or linen, a few pairs of shoes, a few pairs of bikinis, underwear, small make up bag, a pair of jean short, a couple of light silk tops, 2 pairs of shorts and 2 tops for workouts, some accessories in a small jewelry box. A few skincare products in travel size glass bottles, jars. That is all and it’s been more than enough in the last two months on the road… less is more 🙏

Here is an easy 15 minute ab workout that my virtual trainer @taratineka put together for me. 
Circuit -

1. Deadbug 
2. Side plank
3. Mountain Climbers
4. Switch kick drops 
5. Abdominal press with leg drop 
6. Leg drops
7. Russian twist 

30 seconds per exercise, 30 seconds per side ( when needed) 5 mins for one round of exercises. Rest for 30 seconds
* Complete 3 rounds for a total of 15 min ab workout

node.text: This has been a dream for so many years and now it’s a reality ❤️😭 and we get to share it with our child. When we got married 11 years ago we had such an amazing time for a week with family and friends in Dominican Republic. I know it sounds very fancy but the only reason we did it there, is because we couldn’t afford a traditional wedding in Toronto. 😂 So the plan was a destination wedding at an all inclusive resort, everybody pays for themselves and their presence is a gift ( so we asked for no gifts). We had 35 closest family and friends for one week- so much quality time and fun, constant tears of joy. It was absolutely best time ever. We had such a fantastic time, that we promised each other we will celebrate our love and union every 10 years. Here we are 11 years later - having our first vow renewal 🙏 So much has changed in the last 11 years- we have moved countries, we have a child, we had created and sold a successful business, created many other businesses together, made so many new friends, yet one thing remains the same - OUR Love for each other has grown only stronger and deeper. I love you Alex ❤️ you are truly my dream come true @alexikonn
